repoclient:

This package is designed to be installed on the VM to interface with the repoman server. 

To begin, run setup.py.  This will place a repoclient.conf in /etc/repoclient/.  Either edit this file or copy it to ~/.repoclient and insert your usercert, userkey and repository location.


Currently implemented commands:
repoman list [--all]
repoman getuser [--all]
repoman info --name imagename 
repoman save --name imagename [--(any other metadata tags)] [--force]
repoman get --name imagename
repoman delete --name imagename [--force]
repoman update --name imagename [--(any other metadata tags)] [--force]
repoman share (--user username | --group groupname)  --image vmname
repoman unshare (--user username | --group groupname)  --image  vmname


Other metadata tag examples: --hypervisor Xen, --os_variant RHEL, --readonly true
All defaults are set in repoclient.conf, set in /etc/repoclient/repoclient.conf by default (custom may be placed at ~/.repoclient)
